Folder Naming
--> CamalCase with starting letter capital
--> Ex: codin grad, CODINGRAD, Codin Grad --> Unaccetaptable
--> CodinGrad
--> Ex: Fullstack Data Science
--> FullstackDataScience - FDS
File Naming
--> All smallcase letters
--> snake_case
--> Ex: introduction to the course
--> introduction_course
--> Try not to use prepositions, conjunctions, article

FileSystem:
--> Its a software which will map your paths to address on disk
--> FTS, NFTS -- File Tables
--> Paths:
    1. Absolute Path -> Full path -> C:\Users\Vamshi\CodinGrad\sample.txt
        1. Linux Path -> /home/users/vamshi/CodinGrad/sample.txt
        ---> Root Folder(Starting Folder) --> /(Linux) , C:Drive(Windows), G:
        ---> OS Folders --> /usr, /bin, /lib, /sbin, /home, /mnt
        ---> Home Folder --> /home/vamshi (Linux), C:\Users\Vamshi (Windows)
        ---> Command Prompt / Terminal --> Default --> Home Folder
    2. Relative Path -> .\CodinGrad\sample.txt
        ---> pwd --> Linux Command --> Present Working Directory
        ---> w.r.t PWD where is the path --> relative Path

Environment Variables: --> Lookup Table

HOME : its an Environment variable which holds Home Directory
PATH : <Terminal Binary path>:<VS Code Binary path>:<Python Binary Path>:</Python>(echo$PATH)
PYTHONPATH : 
"echo $PATH"

Applications:
1. GUI Applications --> VS Code, Chrome, GitBash GUI, Notepad
2. Non-GUI Applications --> Terminal, GitBash, Python, Java, C/C++, Vim, Nano, emacs, etc.
3. Daemon Applications --> Sleep, Monitor Maintainance, Brightness, System Daemon Applications.

VIM: 
--> Vim is non-gui editor.
--> It will be in 2 modes
    1. Read mode
    2. Write mode
--> By Default vim editor will be in read mode
** cd ~ --> Home path
** ls --> listing all files in current directory
** ls <path> --> list out all contents inside the path
** ls -l --> with more details
** clear --> clearing the screen
** cd .. --> one step back
** rm <filepath> --> will delete specified file
** rm -r <folderpath> --> will delete all files recursively.